An Act relating to the Legislative Service Bureau;
making an appropriation; identifying source of funds;
stating purpose; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: Legislative Service Bureau appropriation
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Legislative
Service Bureau from monies not otherwise appropriated from the ARPA
Administrative Costs Fund created in Section 255.5 of Title 62 of
the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum of Two Hundred Forty-eight Thousand
Dollars ($248,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to pay
obligations that may arise out of contracts during Fiscal Year 2026
related to the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.

Passed the Senate the 20th day of May, 2025.
